caption: This place has a LOT of potential, but I have to say I was kind of underwhelmed. The atmosphere is kind of lackluster. There was an overall feeling of blandness. Maybe the beer taps just needed their actual decorative taps. Besides the awesome BREWCADE sign, there wasn't anything on the walls and it fell kind of flat.

Definitely a nostalgia trip for 80s video games and pinball. There was a pretty nice selection of beer, games were cheap, and they have Killer Queen. They also have foos ball, air hockey, and ski-ball. They don't serve food, but it's in a part of town with lots of take-away options that you can bring in, I presume.

Really great pasta. You could really taste the homemade factor in their tagliatelle and pappardelle. Pasta Sisters is the closest to pasta I had in Bari, Italy where women are sitting in a line, kneading dough for pasta. It was that fresh!
Not too crowded and has a good variety of games and drinks!
Great for a fun date night!
Bartender is awesome and games are cool
Great place to take people that are visiting Oakland for the first time!
Nice 80's stylish bar with arcade games. Good for large parties and hang out with friends.
This spot is the newest hidden gem of oakland old school games that cost 25 cent to 50 cents great drinks and xingones restaurant now! Dude tgis is the spot!
Amazing place. I just love the free play games and it’s even a great place to just hangout.

Definitely a favorite arcade bar, especially before a show at the fox but even as a standalone place to visit for a night out. Good selection and rotation of beers, bartenders move quickly and are pretty awesome, and I swear I was better at Skee Ball when I was 10 than I am now.
Great bar with tasty slushy drinks (and regular fare) and a selection of old and new arcade games

Across the Street from 19th street bart and Make Westing... Connected to The Fox Theatre.... Happy hour before 7pm... Free tokens for being chill... Marvel Vs. Capcom 2... #enoughsaid
Bar game was awesome.
Al ways a great experience when I go there, and really good drinks.

Cool addition to the Oakland bar scene not as vast as their SF location but it gets the job done.my only gripe is their upkeep on their machines (I do fundamentally understand that alcohol and electronics don't mix but even their foose ball table can act finicky) over all a solid bar with cheap drinks. (Don't expect anything fancy)
Great way to ring in the New Year, the only thing that could have made it better, is if they actually served food as well.
